The paper deals with algorithms and lower bounds for a graph problem, specifically the All-Pairs Max-Flow problem. This problem is related to graph theory and network flow, which are typically studied in computer science sub-fields such as data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and network economics (cs.NE).
